<div dir="ltr">Hey Loren,<div><br></div><div style>Great to here you&#39;ve got some time to contribute. Following on from what Angela.. I&#39;d also just point out the 3.0 is really just an API at this stage. We&#39;re at least a month or 2 away from even an alpha UI. So for current projects, 2.7 is probably the way to go. That said we&#39;d love help on 3.0 if you&#39;ve got time to do it.</div>

<div style><br></div><div style>If you&#39;re sending pull requests for 2.x you should make those against the develop branch. Any project you&#39;re developing I&#39;d recommend starting by forking the core repo and keeping track of any changes on a branch in your fork.</div>

<div style><br></div><div style>Robbie. </div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Fri, May 3, 2013 at 9:06 PM, Angela Oduor <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:angela@..." target="_blank">angela@...</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br>

<blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex"><div style="word-wrap:break-word">Hey Loren,<div><br></div><div>This will largely depend on the timeframe and amount of work you need to launch your Ushahidi Project. If this is a time sensitive project, I would advise you to make use 2.7. In as much as we are not building in any new features, we are accepting pull requests, so any new stuff you build in will still go a long way in helping other deployers using 2.7.</div>

<div><br></div><div>3.0 work is ongoing, and you are very welcome to jump on and help. Have a look at</div><div><ul><li>Wiki documentation - <a href="https://wiki.ushahidi.com/display/WIKI/Ushahidi+Platform,+v3.X" target="_blank">https://wiki.ushahidi.com/display/WIKI/Ushahidi+Platform%2C+v3.X</a></li>

<li>Progress on github - <a href="https://github.com/ushahidi/Lamu" target="_blank">https://github.com/ushahidi/Lamu</a> and <a href="https://github.com/ushahidi/Lamu/issues" target="_blank">https://github.com/ushahidi/Lamu/issues</a></li>

<li>Robbie&#39;s blog post a few weeks back - <a href="http://blog.ushahidi.com/2013/04/12/api-wrangling-designing-the-api-for-ushahidi-v3/" target="_blank">http://blog.ushahidi.com/2013/04/12/api-wrangling-designing-the-api-for-ushahidi-v3/</a></li>

